Description . Body length (without antennae) 0.36–0.56 mm ( holotype : 0.47 mm). Colour of the body in alive and alcohol white. Habitus typical of the genus (
Fig. 18
)

Legs chaetotaxy from I to III : tibiotarsi with 7 setae each; femora with 7, 6 , 6 ; trochanters with 3 each; coxae with 3, 4 , 4 ; subcoxae with 0, 2 , 2 . Claws without inner tooth, empodial appendage needle-like and very short (
Figs 27–29
).
